38:28.389 --> 38:31.058
I couldn't exactly find a diamond
on short notice,

38:31.142 --> 38:33.644
but the stone is moon rock.

38:34.812 --> 38:36.689
Um, I brought it back with me,

38:36.772 --> 38:38.899
and I've kind of been keeping it
for a special occasion,

38:38.983 --> 38:40.443
and, well, I--

38:40.526 --> 38:41.944
Luther, it's beautiful.

38:43.237 --> 38:46.574
[emotional instrumental music playing]

38:55.791 --> 38:56.709
Sloane,

38:58.586 --> 38:59.712
will you marry me?

39:06.010 --> 39:06.844
[chuckles]

39:22.818 --> 39:24.195
[emotional music swells]

39:24.278 --> 39:26.155
[energy resonating]

39:45.591 --> 39:46.592
[Diego sighs]

39:47.927 --> 39:49.678
[Lila] Sorry about your robot mum.

39:49.762 --> 39:52.723
-[Diego] She wasn't my real one.
-Okay.

39:54.433 --> 39:56.435
Sorry I lied to you about Stanley.

39:57.937 --> 39:59.355
I miss him too, you know.

39:59.438 --> 40:01.816
I liked that little shit
and his wonky ears.

40:04.568 --> 40:05.820
He deserved better.

40:05.903 --> 40:07.613
Yeah, he did.

40:13.661 --> 40:15.579
Do you know why I brought him to you?

40:15.663 --> 40:17.289
Because you're a sociopath?

40:17.915 --> 40:18.916
No.

40:21.043 --> 40:22.336
Because I'm a coward.

40:23.629 --> 40:26.340
Dropping a kid in your lap
and seeing if you'd reject us and run

40:26.424 --> 40:28.759
felt safer than telling you the truth.

40:30.219 --> 40:31.053
Which is?

40:34.181 --> 40:35.433
I'm pregnant, Diego.

40:42.231 --> 40:43.232
Diego.

40:44.316 --> 40:45.693
I'm pregnant.

40:48.279 --> 40:52.199
I'll pee on whatever stick you want later,
but for now, please, can you just…

41:00.875 --> 41:02.084
[Diego sighs]

41:04.044 --> 41:06.088
My mum put a bullet in my heart.

41:07.006 --> 41:08.007
Did you know that?

41:08.090 --> 41:11.093
Yeah. Five told me. How did you know?

41:11.177 --> 41:12.261
Infinite Switchboard.

41:14.346 --> 41:17.349
I missed your stupid face,
so I snuck in to get a glimpse of you.

41:17.433 --> 41:18.559
And instead…

41:22.646 --> 41:23.647
Thing is,

41:24.982 --> 41:28.569
I'm not gonna be very good
at this… mother thing.

41:29.361 --> 41:30.613
Apples and trees.

41:31.614 --> 41:34.366
But I saw you with Stan,
and you're a good dad.

41:39.163 --> 41:40.998
What do you want from me, Lila?

41:42.917 --> 41:43.751
Okay.

41:44.502 --> 41:45.503
Truth?

41:50.132 --> 41:52.051
I think you should run from me.

41:53.093 --> 41:54.470
[chuckles]

41:54.553 --> 41:55.638
I, um…

41:59.308 --> 42:01.018
I think I'm a bloody mess.

42:01.977 --> 42:06.524
And I think that someone who's…
who never had a family

42:06.607 --> 42:08.692
is in no position to ask for one.

42:10.694 --> 42:12.071
But that's what I want.

42:14.532 --> 42:15.574
With you.

42:25.376 --> 42:26.585
Can I think about it?

42:28.754 --> 42:29.922
[chuckles]

42:31.215 --> 42:32.299
Yeah.

42:32.883 --> 42:33.884
Of course.

42:38.264 --> 42:39.807
[Diego sighs]

42:46.272 --> 42:47.398
[knocks on door]

42:47.481 --> 42:49.441
[Five] Hey, want some company?

42:50.568 --> 42:51.610
[Viktor] Sure.

42:52.653 --> 42:53.612
[Five] Okay.

42:56.323 --> 42:58.200
Hey, that was really nice of you.

42:59.451 --> 43:01.453
Kill Mom so Diego didn't have to.

43:02.246 --> 43:05.499
My God. We are a weird family, aren't we?

43:06.834 --> 43:09.628
Sorry. Yeah, I heard it as I said it.

43:09.712 --> 43:10.546
It's all right.

43:15.509 --> 43:16.719
[Five exhales sharply]

43:19.096 --> 43:21.181
What are we gonna do about Allison?

43:22.224 --> 43:24.602
We're all worried about Allison, but

43:25.853 --> 43:27.146
I'm scared for you.

43:27.896 --> 43:28.856
Seriously?

43:30.608 --> 43:32.693
-Yeah.
-She killed someone.

43:32.776 --> 43:35.112
I was trying to do the right thing
and save Harlan's life.

43:35.195 --> 43:37.990
Do you know why I wanted this last jump
to work so badly?

43:38.073 --> 43:39.491
Because you're old and tired?

43:39.575 --> 43:41.744
Because I slaughtered
a boardroom full of people

43:41.827 --> 43:43.412
to buy our way back here.

43:46.165 --> 43:47.166
Shit.

43:50.669 --> 43:53.005
Little advice from someone
who's been there?

43:54.298 --> 43:55.674
Don't do the math.

43:56.842 --> 43:58.844
That equation does not exist.

43:59.595 --> 44:03.932
There's no "save five Harlans
for every two Claires" formula.

44:04.642 --> 44:07.144
People like us, we will never

44:08.270 --> 44:11.523
save enough lives
to make up for the ones that we take.

44:13.442 --> 44:14.735
I don't accept that.

44:14.818 --> 44:16.153
Then you'll drown.

44:16.654 --> 44:20.824
This is the price of being powerful.
Sometimes we step on ants.

44:22.785 --> 44:26.413
And the sooner you face that,
the safer we'll all be.

44:26.497 --> 44:28.290
What is that supposed to mean?

44:29.291 --> 44:32.586
It means you're very dangerous,
Viktor Hargreeves.

44:33.462 --> 44:36.507
The decisions you make
impact the entire world.

44:37.383 --> 44:40.719
So no matter how benevolent they may seem,

44:41.303 --> 44:43.263
you don't get to make them alone.

44:47.851 --> 44:50.813
You know what they call
a superhero who works alone

44:51.480 --> 44:53.107
and doesn't listen to anybody?

44:54.692 --> 44:56.026
A villain.

44:58.612 --> 44:59.905
I am not a villain, Five.

44:59.988 --> 45:02.658
And, Viktor,
I hope to God you never will be.

45:03.992 --> 45:05.703
But that remains to be seen.

45:06.954 --> 45:07.955
[Five sighs]

45:10.457 --> 45:12.000
No more going rogue.

45:13.001 --> 45:15.754
If you ever need anything,
I'm always here for you.

45:17.381 --> 45:19.258
But lie to us again…

45:21.719 --> 45:23.554
Viktor, I'll kill you myself.

45:24.138 --> 45:27.725
["What Makes You a Man"
by Ninth Wave playing]

45:30.602 --> 45:33.605
I'm glad we made peace. It all worked out.

45:33.689 --> 45:34.690
Yeah.

45:36.150 --> 45:38.318
But we're definitely killing them
in the morning, right?

45:38.402 --> 45:40.195
[Christopher speaks]

45:40.279 --> 45:42.197
And Chris has dibs on knife boy.

45:42.281 --> 45:43.866
No one is killing anyone.

45:44.450 --> 45:45.534
Why not?

45:45.617 --> 45:49.705
We followed your plan,
merged the families, saved the world.

45:49.788 --> 45:51.999
-We don't need them anymore.
-I'm not done yet.

45:52.082 --> 45:53.417
Done what?

45:54.126 --> 45:55.836
That's between me and Dad.

45:58.630 --> 45:59.798
You made a deal with Dad?

46:01.133 --> 46:02.134
Maybe.

46:04.928 --> 46:05.846
Fine. I'm done.

46:05.929 --> 46:07.222
-Sit down.
-No.

46:07.306 --> 46:09.516
We don't recognize your authority anymore.

46:09.600 --> 46:13.395
You're a terrible leader
with no loyalty to anyone but yourself.

46:13.479 --> 46:15.606
You don't speak for Christopher.

46:15.689 --> 46:17.691
